
-- Phase 1: Add Priority Eastern European Languages
-- Ukrainian - Critical given current global importance (40M+ speakers)

-- Hungarian - Major EU language, unique Finno-Ugric family (9M+ speakers)

-- Romanian - Major Romance language in Eastern Europe (19M+ speakers)

-- Bulgarian - South Slavic representation (7M+ speakers)

-- Croatian - Major Balkan language (5M+ speakers)

-- Phase 2: Add Priority Asian Languages
-- Indonesian - 4th most populous country, 270M+ speakers

-- Mongolian - Central Asian representation, unique script tradition

-- Burmese - Major Southeast Asian language (33M+ speakers)

-- Nepali - South Asian mountain region (16M+ speakers)

-- Khmer - Cambodia, unique Austroasiatic family (16M+ speakers)
